    "abstract": "<jats:title>Abstract</jats:title>\n                <jats:sec>\n                  <jats:title>Objectives</jats:title>\n                  <jats:p>To evaluate if antibodies induced by infection with a different SARS-CoV-2 virus strain neutralize the P.1 variant.</jats:p>\n                </jats:sec>\n                <jats:sec>\n                  <jats:title>Methods</jats:title>\n                  <jats:p>Convalescent sera from 60 individuals following a documented SARS-CoV-2 infection were assayed for neutralizing antibody titer against both strains.</jats:p>\n                </jats:sec>\n                <jats:sec>\n                  <jats:title>Results</jats:title>\n                  <jats:p>Fifty-six and 50 sera were positive for neutralizing antibodies against the ancestral and P.1 strains, respectively. Neutralization titers were higher against the ancestral strain, but in the majority of patients differences did not differ by more than a single dilution.</jats:p>\n                </jats:sec>\n                <jats:sec>\n                  <jats:title>Conclusions</jats:title>\n                  <jats:p>\n                    Neutralizing antibodies that were generated following infection with SARS-CoV-2 B.1.1.28 were effective\n                    <jats:italic>in vitro</jats:italic>\n                    , against the SARS-CoV-2 P.1. variant.\n                  </jats:p>\n                </jats:sec>",
